Well I presume my father would be but I can't really remember. And - after that I don't think there was anything in it - I think it just depended how my mother felt probably or who was nearest or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Where did your younger brother sit before he could feed himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 My brother was the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember him when he was not old enough to sit at the table with you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I can't remember it, we were too ne
ar in age. You see. You see, there was only four years between us and I - I can't remember my brother - no, I can't remember him very small at all - or my sister if it comes to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. Definitely not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 For what reason - can you give me your feelings about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Don't know it was - it was her makeup I think as much as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she not encourage you to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You never felt you were coaxed to talk to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. Never - never - never remember being able to talk to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did you feel a need to at times - did you wish at that time that you could or weren't you conscious of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I wasn't conscious of any thing it's only since when I've looked back I've though a
bout it. Of course, you know, you take things for granted when you're small and - I don't suppose I thought of it really that way but - I suppose I thought that everybody else was the same. I didn't notice that anybody else was any different and there was
 such a gap, more of a gap between parents and children then and more so in my case because - partly because my mother was so much older - I think that had something to do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So much older than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And so much older than we were, you see, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 She had you late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. I think that made a difference too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, we're not an affectionate family - we don't show it. None of us have ever done, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You felt there was nothing you could have talked to her about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I never talked to her about anything as far as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Th
at's difficult because - he - I think he could have been but he didn't get the chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 In what way do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you see, it all comes back to - the difficulties between father and mother you see, they didn't get on awfully well - they didn't quarrel, they weren't that sort of people, but they just - well, ignored one another and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You feel that your father wasn't around because of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you see, it's - see when my mother got - disgruntled about him and we knew that she was do
ing so much for us and she sort of - got us on her side, that's the only way I can explain it and - we sort of didn't take very much notice of him and it's a thing that's worried me a lot since. Because - yes, because - things shouldn't have been like tha
t
 and - I didn't realize it at the time but - we could have been very much closer to my father in a lot of ways but we didn't get the chance of being young we didn't see it and I think I could have been very friendly with him because after my mother died -
 although that was very much later - dad and I really did get very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Got to know each other a bit then did you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. It was a pity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Better to find out late than not at all isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. But it was too late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But you did have a little bit of time left to get to know each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, for - eight years he lived after my mother died. Unfortunately mostly the war years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Which were difficult years anyway weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You said you didn't have much to do
 with your father and were probably influenced in this by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
But did he show you any affection in any way - did you get the impression as a child that he was affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well he might have done when we were very small - so
 small that I can't remember now. But - I don't - I think he might have done if he'd had the chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Difficult to answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It is really isn't it. We were expect
ed to do - as you were told and - she was the one who made the rules and the laws and you just had to abide by them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brother and sister in certain ways - did you feel there was any behaviour that was expected of you in the way you acted towards your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't really know what that means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you ever remember your mother saying now behave like this to your brother and sister - can you remember ever being told off or encouraged or spoken to about your relationships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, I can, because I never got on with my brother and there were always quarrels going on and - I don't suppose in a big way really, but I know there was ill feeling and, you see, he was the only boy and
 he was the baby and my mother spoilt him. And always took his part. Well, I can't remember any specific occasion - it's just a sort of thread running through the whole thing and there was ill feeling there. And I know my father sensed it. From things he 
said afterwards. That he would like to have had an influence over my brother but he didn't get the chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Your mother took over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, and it certainly showed later when he was a ill for so long. Life was terribly difficult then. She certainly did spoil him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How old was he when he was taken ill - after the accident you were mentioning?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
He was about - well he was twenty-one, you see, he'd come back from serving his time. Well he'd wasted his time while he was with the Metrovic so of cour
se they didn't keep him. When he came home he had to look for a job. Well you see in the 1920's things weren't too good, he was at home a long time and then - they began to notice that there was something wrong with him. And he went to the doctor but our 
d
octor was an elderly man and he didn't know anything about this new fangled complaint that had come out - none of us did. So of course he didn't get the treatment he might have done, I know that now people who get entephilitus don't have such a bad time b
ecause they know more about it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No, don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be? Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life? Can you ever remember them saying certain things were important in life and what their hopes for you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can't say really. They hoped we'd get on in life I suppose and - they wee strict as regards bringing us up, I mean, they - very strict as - in regard things right and wrong and - making you behave yourself and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 These were important things you felt to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh yes, they were, yes, they were important things. Yes, my mother was very strict. That way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Swearing was unknown in those days amongst ordinary - well, people like us. It's only lately that you get it thrust down your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 throat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  all the time I don't - never heard a wrong word in my home - not all my life - 
no. Never. Neither my father nor my mother. My father was very funny - you see. What he did outside I do not know - I could say that he didn't say anything even then but I wasn't there to see but I only know there was nothing said at home. But if dad got 
r
attled he always used to say - damn twice. And - and I remember telling that to somebody once and she said, damn, damn. And I said, no, not damn, dann. Damn twice. And my mother used to say - now, now, but he used to giggle. Yes, you see dad had a - which
 I discovered later - quite a sense of humour which my mother hadn't, you see, but - just in the short time after she died I could see that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You appreciated that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. Yes. He had - mother had no sense of humour but he had and I think he used to say that to annoy her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When grown ups you children were not allowed to join in were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Ye
s, we were - I'm just trying to think. We weren't - it doesn't seem very clear to me what did happen. Must have been something. Because I know I was terrified of ever being found in the wrong. I suppose we got slapped - must have been that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Who would have slapped you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Never your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh no, dad never laid a finger on us but my mother would. Well you see he left all the controlling of us to my mother you see, he didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would she have slapped you for many things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, not many things, no, she wasn't - hard in that way. She would - give you a good telling off that's what you got mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh pretty awful. Pretty awful because she made you really feel terrible.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you remember how you felt when she slapped you for something - what were your emotions then as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Some - I don't know we ever had any - you just took - we accepted it and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You didn't query it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, oh no. No. No, well you took it that she was right because that was the way you were brought up to feel - you didn't question her. I've questioned her since she's dead. But never - never then
, that's why I think if - you know, if - it's all it was all so - I don't know - I can't understand how it was that we were as we were when I came older and began to - think of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Not very. We bought one another little presents if we had a few coppers and I remember we used to but my father a little present when it was his birthday, 'cos his birthday was on Empire Day and Empire Day was a great day in those days. We used to buy hi
m a little present - handkerchief or some small thing - you know, when we were very small and then of course we grew out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have ever bought your mother a little present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We must have done but I can't connect it with her the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Just the fact that it was Empire Day might make it stick in your memory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, it does stick out and yet my mother's birthday was the same day as mine but I can't remember that we ever did anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have had a party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, we never had parties as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would your parents have bought you presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Probably they did, they must have done but I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was there anything special for tea on that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We might have had but that could be possible but we never had anybody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That doesn't stick out in your mind very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you remember anything you did with your father and mother together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I can't really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember any set pattern, wheth
er you went out or had Christmas at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, we didn't go out - we always were at home together - always. And we never seemed to have anyone there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You didn't have relatives or friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. But we were there. We - and we were always ex
pected - even when we grew older - we were expected to be there. On Christmas Day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
We had a piano. My mother had a piano and she had that - you see, she had that before she was married because she had a home before she was married because one of the troubles was that when they were married it was my mother's home. That we lived in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was this the house that you were talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 The back - she owned the house. No, she - we - I did
n't live in any of - I was going to say I didn't live in any of the houses mother lived in before she got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But she had a house of her own in her own name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. She had all - all her furniture and that and the piano belonged to her and I know my father learned to play. She paid for him, lessons when he was quite young to learn to play the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When they were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you see, it's going back into history again, it doesn't really matter one way or the other but she knew hi
m from when he was a boy of about sixteen and he was keen on music because he sang in Grantham church choir, so she paid for him to have lessons on this piano - he didn't get very far. So we had the piano when we were small. But during one of the periods 
w
hen dad hadn't got so much to do the piano was sold. And her cutlery and a lot of things that she had - the jewellery or any bits of jewellery she had and anything she sold them. When cash was short. So that's a long time ago I scarcely remember what the 
p
iano looked like but I remember it was there and I do remember the evening that my brother was christened and I can remember people being there and the candles lighted on the piano, just vaguely because I was allowed to pop in and see this before I went t
o bed. I just remember that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
While you had the piano did you ever make music together as a family and was there anyone who sang in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. Oh, that reminds me, they had another piano after that. Yes, we had a piano afterwards and I 
learnt for a few weeks, but you see, when I was at school they were intent on me passing exams and one thing and another so I really didn't have time to practise so I gave it up after about - quarter I think I had. Then my sister learnt for a little while
 and - if anybody came that could play we'd have sing-songs. We had lots of music - sheet music, oh yes. Songs and books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you say you had quite a few musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well if anybody came in who could play the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This would be an automatic thing would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, we'd all start singing songs - we had student song books and we've - I've still got these student song book in there. Then we got - then we moved here you see, coming to a smaller house we had to get rid of a lot. Yes. 
But all - and my mother was very fond of singing and - that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she used to sing herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 She - you know - only - in the house and that she - she liked singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would she ever sing solo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. Oh no, she wasn't a sin
ger in that sense but she liked songs and she enjoyed the music and hearing people sing and if anybody came who could play she'd persuade them to play and we'd have songs - we'd all sing and - we liked that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What sort of games do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Indoor games - things like snakes and ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh we always - we all had ludo and things like that as children. We had -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember your parents joining in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well they must have taught us even
 if they didn't play with us but I remember we had ludo and draughts. Dad used to play draughts and dominoes with us and dad taught us how to play cards. We played the ordinary children games in cards like snap and strip and things like that and dad taugh
t us how to play whist. Yes, he taught us how to play whist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 He would play with you quite a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. And he and my brother used to play cribbage - I remember that because we had two cribbage boards and he used to play that. Oh we used to pl
ay games and - and we had other games we used to play as well - writing games. And what - I don't know what one was called - but we used to make a list of different categories of things and people, like rivers and lakes and countries and - just your names
 and all things like that and then we'd choose a letter and then we all had to write down opposite the - something beginning with that letter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How many people could think of things b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 ginning with that - yes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That's right. And then we used to call
 them out and the one that got the only one got the most and one - if everybody got it you only got one each. We used to - I don't know what we used to call that game. But we were very fond of that. Yes. I can't think of any other - oh, consequences and t
hings like that we used to play, you know, those games, we liked those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh yes, always. My father was very fond of books. Yes, we had a - a nice - bookcase there and a - when we were very young - they - well we've s
till got some of them, those gold back books on the top there, you see, there was the Everyman Library and I think it was Collins, and they brought wonderful books out for about a shilling. And even those leather books in there were only two shillings. An
d dad had - a bookcase full of them. But of course when we moved - we couldn't keep them, we gave them to, I forget }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 now who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  it was, but somebody came and took a lot of them away to some club or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But your father did read a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 He did - read a lot, he was a great reader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, well she never seemed to have time to read. She was always busy doing things. But my father really was unfortunate. He should have had a better start in life. You see, when he was y
oung they lived in Grantham he left school, he went into the Post Office and was really - would have done very well. But when they came here, his father insisted on him coming here, you see, well of course - and I - you see, in those days there wouldn't b
e
 such a thing as a transfer so he had to come here and start all over again but he never got the same chance again. Well dad was very good clerically but he never really had the opportunity because, you see, he was Treasurer and Secretary of these things 
I told you about the other day, these gymnastic things, he did all the arranging and he was very good at that sort of thing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And the Masonic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
And - and I think that's why he did a lot of things for them because he really was very good that way but - it was a great pity, he never really had the chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 The potential was there but the chance wasn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. No, it was his father's fault. They should have left him there but the old man wanted him here and - that's all there was to it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have had newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, we always had the Echo - the old days when it was pink and a ha'penny. He always had the Echo. But we never went in for magazines very much. And yet there were good magazines out then, I often think of those - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Strand{\*\xmlclose} and - you never see anything like it now, they were paper backs but they were thick and they had lots of stories in. Well dad had Harmsworth and Pearsons and he had them bound and we had a whole shelf full of bound volumes of Pearsons 
and Harmsworth magazines and I used to read, there were - you see, there'd be a serial in but in the bound book of about a years things, it'd go on. And I can remember sitting up at night and reading - what was it - Seniors of the Night and it was - what 
y
ou'd call a horrific story of - things happening in Venice and the Bridge of Sighs and I know there was a picture of a man spread out flat and somebody boring a hole with a brace and bit in his chest. And going to bed and have - having fits while I was in
 bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would your parents have ever read aloud to each other or to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember a funeral in the family as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. You see, my - mother's parents died in Manchester and my mother went to 
the funeral and my other Grandmother didn't die until I was - see, 1916 - I was eighteen you see, and that of course wasn't in my own home, it was in their home and I just remember going - attending the funeral. That was all. - Because, you see, there was
 another child - there was a girl between my sister and me but she only lived six months, you see, and that was before I could remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You don't recall that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember your grandmother's funeral - what people were wearing a
nd anything about the day in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, not really, only of course then everybody strictly wore black. I was only thinking the other day you don't see black anywhere now. I got in a bus and the woman sitting opposite to me, she was all in black and I noticed it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 particularly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
. Yes. Yes. O I do - one - one thing I do remember about it was, I hadn't got a black dress and - I must have got a black coat from somewhere although I don't remember - and I had a dark green dress and I put the green dress on
 and my mother carried on - she said, you can't go to a funeral in a green dress. I didn't know why and I still don't know why but I went in the green dress - it was very dark green and I can just remember going in the green dress and of course there were
 horses in those days and I do remember as we were coming up a street they stopped and the carriage door opened and a lady got in with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 wreath}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 . She come from over the water and she was late so she met the funeral so they stopped on the way and picked her u
p. I can remember that. But beyond that I don't remember very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Never went shopping with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Not until I was quite - 'til I was big enough to do the shopping - some of bit. I don't remember being taken out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When you were bigger would you have gone with your mother to do it or ....?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well when I was older she'd send me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember going out shopping for clothes with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I must have done mustn't I - I must have done because after all she'd have to take me for shoes and things. I can't recall anything particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, for walks to the park sometimes he - we would go with him. 'Cos he was very fond of the parks. He was a man that really belonged to the country - he loved all the things in the park and the ducks and - he used to take his p
ockets full of - nuts for the squirrels which I don't suppose are there now and - bread and things for the ducks - to feed the ducks was a great thing when we were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You enjoyed that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. And then I remember when the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Seften{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} lake was f
rozen over, he took us to see the skaters and they had - they must have had - Chinese lanterns or something - there were all lights and it was lovely. Yes, it was nice. Yes, I remember that. Yes, dad used to take us to the park. And every Sunday morning r
egularly he took us down to see his mother and - father. Every Sunday morning we had to go and as regular as every Sunday morning there was a row when we got back because he always brought us in late for dinner. Regular thing on a Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do yo
u remember any outings at all with your parents apart from the ones you've told me about - what about Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Occasionally on a Bank Holiday we did go out. Now - I can remember - going over the water to Secombe Station, now - where would be go
ing? Oh at one time - dad knew some other young fellows that had tents on the common at Morton when it first started and they'd go for the weekend. And if it was a Bank Holiday we would go. 'Cos I can remember waiting for the train coming back on Morton s
t
ation and there was a train called Park and we could never get on it. And I never understood the mystery of this train that went to Park and why we couldn't get on it. And that's a proof to you that you couldn't question my mother very easily. Of course n
ow I know what it was - because we wanted a train that brought us back to Secombe so that we could get the boat 'cos the Park one stopped at the Park station in Birkenhead but I didn't know that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And you wouldn't have been able to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, well 
you didn't because you see you'd be so afraid of - being told - layers for meddlers and crutches for lame ducks or something like that. See, that was her protective way I think of not - she didn't want to answer you and so she said something that - settle
d it, you know, didn't say any more - yes. 'Cos you know, I think really - what I meant by saying I didn't think I would be very much use over this is that my mother was not a very usual person. You might get another person of my age who's - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 who's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  experienc
e was entirely different. I don't think mine is typical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But it is one aspect you see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, could be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 There are probably more people like your mother then than there are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh - oh that would be true - yes. Yes. Well I know my mothe
r was a difficult person because she didn't get on with her own family. She kept away from them, you see. She came to live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}. And none of the others did. Two sisters went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. She came here. And - and her brother was in the Navy and in
 the 1914 war his family came to Liverpool then and they still are round about - but until then she was the only one here and she did keep away from her people. I think she got on with her mother but she didn't get on with her father. And - so I think the
re must have been something a bit unusual about her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
This trip on the train we were just talking about - would this have been the sort of thing you'd done on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. And I think occasionally we might have gone - to Hardon. Or Puckley 
where I was born to see - relatives there because she had a lot of cousins and people and we'd go and see them - spend the day there and - 'course we went the same way. We went on that - I'm wondering if I'm getting mixed up with the train to Morton - whe
t
her it were when we went to Hardon we went to Secombe station, I don't remember. But I know we used to - and - we had a dog. We had a dog and - and - silly things you remember - I could remember lifting the dog up in my arms over the turnstile and him str
uggling to get - I suppose I hadn't the sense to let him go underneath - I lifted him up and got him over the top. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh yes. Yes, we were lucky that way 'cos sometimes I used to go to some relatives or other
 of my mother's over in North Wales but most often we went to Uttoxeter in Staffordshire. We got to know some people there and - they were very good and if my parents couldn't go we used to be put in charge of the guard at Lime Street with a little tip - 
w
hen we got to Crewe he'd pass us over to a porter who would take us down with the luggage and on the subway and up on to the North Starrordshire line to wait for the train 'cos you always had to change you see, we went on the - it was the five twenty-five
 for years, the Loughton train to Crewe. And then we changed into the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}North Stafford{\*\xmlclose}
 train and we went to Uttoxeter and we used to spend holiday there. Sometimes we'd be there for the whole - well a whole month or more we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was this mainly with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. Mostly on our own. Mostly on our own. And when my sister got this nerve trouble she was there for about three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 As a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, well - well she would be - how old was she - about ten or so but from when we were
 - how it happened - the friend who lived there was in Liverpool when my brother had scarlet fever. And when he was due to come home this friend said, I'll take the two girls and keep them. Yes, while you look after him and that was the beginning of it. A
nd after that we went for years and years. The last time I was there was 1920. And - and then we didn't go again and they died and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We were talking about holiday and you said you went to Uttoxeter quite a bit?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did all you children go - your brother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, at different times we must all have been there - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When you went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} occasionally would your father and mother have come to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think so. They - they would take us and leave us there and then pe
rhaps - come and bring us home again but they didn't - didn't stay, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What would you have done on your holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh well, in Uttoxeter there was a big garden - great big garden and there was a swing from a tree and we used to - and then we got
 to know other children there and we used to play in their gardens and play in back garden and then - it was a railway junction and the trains were a tremendous }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16341641\charrsid793154 
interest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  - used to watch the trains - they did a lot of shunting there and we used to watch the
m, we knew the numbers of all the trains, we knew the names of all the drivers and - we used to watch for them out and - we used to go down the goods yard and - of course the goods were delivered by horse }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 drawn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  lorries then - they had gorgeous }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 horses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  - bea
utiful you know, chubby fat chestnut horses - lovely. And we used to walk down the goods yard and see the horses and - and then there was a market day on a Wednesday. All the people from the farms round about used to come in in the traps and bring all the
 
- their goods and they had big baskets with white cloths over with butter on a cabbage leaf, you know. Pats of butter with a beautiful pattern on because they - whatever they call those things they pat them with. They'd have - thistles or acorns or someth
i
ng. Lovely golden butter on these things - I can remember that. And the - well the market people used to come every Wednesday and then there was a racecourse there and sometimes we'd be there when the races were on and - when the races weren't on we used 
to go walks along the racecourse and gather mushrooms, I remember that. And I don't - think it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You didn't have many dull moments did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We didn't. We loved going there. And then when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have gone to the coast in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
North Wales{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, it wasn't near the coast you see, it's - not - not really very near. Where we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It's not near enough to go down to the beach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No. Oh no, we just - it was just a case of - being in the country with the other people, playing in the fields and - and walking - round -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Just a change from the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That's all, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
When you were a child how did you spend Saturdays - were they different to any other day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well you always had things to do on a Saturday,
 see, I used to hate Saturday because we always had to do things in the house, we all had our jobs to do. And a lot of other children were out playing well, we - we would have things to do. We always did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have a set job that you had to do r
egularly to help in the house or would you take it in turns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well - whatever we were told to do we had to do. We were made to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This would be all Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, all Saturday morning we - you'd be busy doing things or doing messages
 or - something like that but you always had to do something. And then of course when you got older and you got homework from school you had that to do and we used to spend a lot of time doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 On a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well if I didn't do it on Friday night I had to do it on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was there anything particular you did on Saturday afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well we'd go to the park with dad perhaps or - something like that. I can't think of any particular - or take the dog out or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, well, it was the fashion then to have something different on a Sunday - something extra on a Sunday we always had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you play the games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents thing it wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
My mother did. Yes, my mother did, you didn't do anything - 'cos I remember once a cousin coming from Manchester and playing ball outside the house - there was actions. You didn't do anything like that. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not regularly. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What denomination would it have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That would have been church of England I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How often would you say they might have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well - my father didn't go because this - boys club t
hing that he belonged to had a - a meeting on a Sunday evening. About sevenish I should think. And he used to go there. They had - so his - he was - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about Sunday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well on Sunday morning he always used to go down to - until his
 father died in 1913 - he went down there every Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You were taken down to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, while we were young we were but afterwards we didn't go. But he always went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Your mother would go to an evening service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Occasionally but not very often - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you go to a service at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Not - I didn't go to church so much but we always had to go to Sunday school on a Sunday afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And this was Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there any Sunday school outings that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
They had them but I can't remember going to any. 'Cos I can remember as long - as long ago as when they had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  drawn wagonettes and I can remember going somewhere - but I don't remember where it was - in a horse drawn 
wagonette. I can remember being in it and I can remember the horses because there were long seats on either side and you sat facing but I don't know where we went to - it couldn't have been very far and I don't know whether - that must have been to do wit
h Sunday school. But I don't remember.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You went to a wide open space where they let you loose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, and you just played round, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
What other social activities organised by the church did you take part in - did you belong to the choir or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No, because you see I only went to the - to Sunday school - didn't got to church much at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, they didn't but strangely - strage you should mention that. There was - a - Primitive Me
thodist chapel at the corner of the street. Still there but rebuilt. And they had a Band of Hope. And I - we must have known somebody who went to it and we persuaded mother to let us go. So we used to go to the Band of Hope and sing all the temperance son
g
s and hymns and - I don't know what good it was really, I don't know much what we did but girls used to get up and recite poetry. Yes. And I know you had a little card and you had it marked if you were there but - I don't remember anybody saying anything 
b
ut they must have done. But I know it was called a Band of Hope and we went. And we sang the - the temperance hymns. Dare to be a Daniel wasn't it? That's - and then - that's about all I can remember. Dare to stand alone dare to have a purpose firm and da
re to make it known. And Father, dear father, come home with me now, the clock in the steeple strikes one. Something about poor Benny is worse and then in the end poor Benny was dead and gone to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 angels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  of light - something like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So you didn't belong to any club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was grace said at meals in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, we had to say our prayers every night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was your mother the one who taught you and saw to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, she must have done when we were young but you see it'd become a habit - that we just did it - what - you know, without - always done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you ever have family prayers together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I wouldn't say he did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I think he was Liberal - years ago when there was just Liberals and Conservatives but I think his ideas were more Labour afterwards although he was very critical even so, he wasn't a committed man at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We didn't go in blindly you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No, and he - I don't think he sided very much with - anybody really. But he was - agreement with - when Labour started and things were so difficult 
for a working man he was very much in favour of trades unions and that sort of thing. But he lived long enough to become very critical of them and he certainly would be critical of them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember him talking about who should govern the cou
ntry and whether he thought the working man had a square deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No, only insofar as I've said, that he took interest in the trades union movement - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When he was a Liberal really - when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes - when - yes, when we wore young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And he felt this was a good thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh he thought it was a good things because certainly people had a very bad deal then and he agreed with what the trade unions started out to do. But - he didn't agree with what came afterwards because 
- and he certainly wouldn't agree with things they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you think of any reason why he held these views - why he tended to go towards the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I suppose he - he saw it amongst workmen and - in the way men were treated and -
 I suppose he saw it on the docks, the way dock labourers used to be treated. Things were very bad but of course things have gone to the opposite stream now, so that the people you were really sorry for then, you're annoyed about now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, she didn't bother at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she have any views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You've no idea what she felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, she never bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember your parents voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
They must have done but I don't remember much about it - all I can remember about elections in those days was they used to have a torchlight procession but I can't remember now whether that was a - a general election or a local one but I know there was 
always a torchlight procession - I don't remember seeing it but I remember all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 On the day of the election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. But I don't know which it was to do with. 'Cos I - I suppose I wasn't really very interested you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 In some plac
es at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers - do you know if your father felt himself under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I've never heard of that. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was your father a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And your mother wouldn't have done either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did they take part in any political activity other than at election time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think they were that interested in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time in the evenings - you mention that your father read a great deal and that your mother mostly was busy and didn't seem to have time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
She didn't really. And of course - well, in the early days, you see, dad had this club which he went to three or four nights in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This was the boys club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. And then you see, apart f
rom the definite club nights they had this league for gymnastic things and they had competi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 ti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 ons which were arranged for other nights and then of course there were meetings of the judges association and the league things, so that he practically had somethi
ng on every night, I never remember him being at home. He was mostly out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And what would your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh she'd be in sewing or doing something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No she didn't seem to - she didn't - no, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 About - half past five to six I think, something like that. Six probably.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did he attend any clubs
 for his own amusement or any pubs - you said he was a teetotaler but he enjoyed his glass of port?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
That was only on occasions you know but - different occasions or Christmas time or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did he take part in any sport - you mentioned the g
ymnastic club, but did he take part in any sport at all.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No, he didn't. He didn't do anything only this gymnastic things, he did a bit of that but he didn't - take any other part. He liked to watch. Yes, he - he used to go to watch the football and the cricket in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Sefton{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Oh yes. In the winter, you see, there were a lot of amateur clubs that played cricket on what we called the old farm field in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Sefton{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and I used to go with him quite often because I played hockey at school and the positi
ons in the football were the same so I used to go with him. And - they used to get a good crowd, about three deep, round that - that pitch there and I remember somebody kicking the ball into my face once and I had to be picked up in pieces. Yes, and - and
 then in the summer he used to go and watch Sefton cricket playing, when they played at home. He was very keen on cricket.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So he was conscious of sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh yes. Very. Yes, and he knew - although he never went to the big games of Everton and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose} or anything he knew all about the players. Yes, and he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  a Liverpudlian. He supported {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool
{\*\xmlclose} but I don't ever remember him going. But he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did he ever go to races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did he ever place a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think he ever did. If he did I didn't get to know about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs - boot, sick or funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh my mother had some insurances like everybody had when we were children. But I don't remember much
 about them and I don't remember what happened to them but I know she was in some insurances. So - well I think it was only about a penny a week in those days or something. She was. Somebody came and collected it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you get on with your bro
ther and sister - you squabbled a bit with your brother - but your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh we all got on quite well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You said you felt closer to your sister than your bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, much. Although I can't say we were ever very friendly - we just 
accepted each other. That's about all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You were just there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
As a child who did you play with - would it have been your sister or your brother or neighbours mainly or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well as far as we ever were allow
ed out to play I suppose it would be other children in the street but then my mother was very - particular. If we ever got out it was an unusual occasion - she didn't let us out. She didn't like us playing with other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 She preferred you to play amongst yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, she was very much like that you know, because she used to talk about other children racing the streets and she wouldn't have her children racing the streets. She was very particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When you did go out it would have b
een mainly in the streets - you wouldn't have gone elsewhere or somebody else's garden or yard or other homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No. We were never allowed to go into anyone else's home. That was a strict rule that you didn't go into anybody else's house, I can't telly you why but we weren't allowed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
What games did you play - can you remember some of the outdoor games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh the games all children used to play in those days. Skipping, you know, skipping rope and - ball - all sort of ball games 
up against the wall and - well of course children don't do it as much now because suppose the traffics against it. But we used to play those and battledore and shuttlecock and - we had hoops and - then we used to play hopscotch a lot, you know, the old fa
shioned hopscotch, then we used to play hopscotch with a ball. That's about all I can remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It was trouble if you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would she get cross with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would she get sufficiently cross with you to make you not get dirty again?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you had to be careful, you had the thought all the while that you'd be in - hot water when you got back - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased - you mentioned your mother 
forbad you to go into anyone's home - did either of your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. I do remember there was a family that lived near to us and one time and - we were not supposed to have anything to do with them. 
Well - the - the girl was disagreeable - disagreeable child altogether and - I can quite understand that. But that was the only one I can remember - otherwise she didn't bother 'cos after all we knew - you knew the children even if you didn't go out to pl
ay with them 'cos you probably went to school with them. But there was one family that she was very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was it the fact that the child was disagreeable or was there any other reason?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh I think it was because she was - she was a nasty sort of child
. I can remember her because I was rather frightened of her myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was it because she was rougher than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I don't know what it is - there was something wrong about her - I don't know what it was, but something disagreeable and I was a bit afraid of her so I - I didn't mind not playing with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It was one of the rules you accepted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you belong to any youth organizations as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any
 hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, you see, when I was at Aigburth you see you mostly had homework that kept you busy all the evening. Well a couple of nights a week you might stay for a hockey practice or - rounders or tennis in the summer and by the time you'd got ho
me, you see, after all in those days we had to walk from Princes Road to Aigburh Vale to school and back. Well by the time - see it was a couple of miles - by the time you'd played a hockey match and then come home and had your tea, drawn your breath and 
done your homework it was time to go to bed so we didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you keep any pets - you mentioned you had a dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
We had a dog, yes. We had a cat once think, but mostly the cats we had were later. We had cats later but we had a dog once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you go fishing or walks or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh we had bicycles. After I went down to Aigburth I got a bicycle and then my sister got one, see after that we didn't have to walk so much we had the b
icycles to come - but then of course when we had the bicycles we used to take rides round the park on the way home. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Who would you go bicycling with - mainly with your sister, apart from going to school? Would you use then for amusement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 We
 would occ - we - we went over the water sometimes and - cycled out to Irbey or Haswell or Thursteston or somewhere sometimes on a Saturday afternoon but only - by ourselves, not with anybody else. No, we never - we didn't belong to any - thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You played hockey - was this a regular thing for you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, you see, when I went to Aigburth every form had its own hockey team, you were chosen, and I played for my own form and eventually I played for the school and then we had matches with o
ther - similar schools. And then after I left school I joined the hockey club and I was in that until the war came and - and I went away from home, then I didn't - but - well I - I think it fizzled out afterwards - I never heard anymore about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But hockey was the main thing as far as sport was concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did you go any concerts, theatres, music halls or cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Not a great deal, we generally went to the pantomime at Christmas time. And somet
imes, if there was a Shakespeare play on - at one of the theatres, it would be arranged from school and we would go. I remember going to the rep - Repatory theatre as the Playhouse was called then. And - we saw whatever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 Shakespeare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  play we were doing if - 
anybody came and did it we - we went there. Yes. And - not otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No music halls or variety shows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. No, my mother wasn't very keen on theatres at all so that was about all we were allowed to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well when we were very small we didn't have any pocket money because my mother used to say I can - I'll buy you whatever sweets you're to have. So we didn't get any pocket money. But when I went to Aigburth I used to get the magnificent sum of 
a shilling a week and out of that it used to cost me tenpence for my tram fare because I used to come home for my lunch and get a tram one way but I couldn't get a tram all the way home, I had to get a tram that went Park Road way and then I had to walk u
p Hill Street so I had tuppence left. But of course it meant they paid all bills and things but that's all that I ever had in my pocket for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You didn't have anything extra on the Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did anyone outside the home help your moth
er look after her house or family? You mentioned she had some .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
We did have - help of different sorts - different women used to come in and they - you'd have a woman for so long and then she'd fade out and then you'd have another one. With no - 
you know, they never stayed - because they only came in and did the heavy - part of the - the heavy floors and steps and - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Would your mother have had any friends or neighbours who came in to help her with the children or to do any thing for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No, she wouldn't - she'd manage.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I don't remember my mother ever being ill. I don't. No, I never remember my mother being ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You don't remember your brother being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did your parents have any relatives living nearby - your father's parents were living near enough for you to be taken to see them on the Sunday morning - your mother's people weren't in Liverpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Were there any other relatives apart from your grandparents on your father's side that lived nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. Because there was only - my grandparents and two daughters - oh, and a son, but they all lived at home - they all lived together. You see, there was nowhere else to go to. We had no other people to visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You saw those regularly of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. Quite regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well, no, very - in the sense of people visiting they didn't ever have anybod
y. They knew people and I think that most of them were people that they'd known years before before probably my mother was married and she used to talk about them but I don't remember meeting them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you think they shared the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 so far}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
 as they were friends they had before they were married they did share them. And then afterwards of course if dad knew anybody well he - well, some of the men belonging to this club - this gymnastic thing - used to come to the house sometimes b
ut generally if they wanted to know something or to see him about something. They never came for the evenings or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not for any social evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
So apart from the friend your mother had before she was married and spoke of she really didn't have any friends that you knew of that she kept in touch with after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Not - not - a long time ago - but she did have a friend later on that she was friendly with for - quite a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would this be past 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, much past that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
If you did have anyone in would they be offered anything to eat or drink when they came
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I suppose they might have been. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
You said you mostly ate in the kitchen but if you had visitors you ate in another room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
In the other rooms, yes, well people must have come odd times but I can't really remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did anyone call in casually without an invitation or can't you remember that?;;

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I think people must have come occasionally but - well, I know
 this that sometimes when people came we were chased out. Because you weren't - you weren't to be listening in to the conversation of the older people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did neighbours ever call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Mother never - never made a neighbour. We never had a neighbour 
'til we came here. And have we've -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You said you were delighted with them - they were very kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, we've been wonderfully lucky but we never had a neighbour before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 People often tell us in those days they made their own amusements - what
 do you think your parents did when they did have friend in or they went out - would they have made music or played games or talked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, I suppose that would have been it, if there was a piano that - people would tend to go towards the piano and - and that - people did make their own amusements if they- if they did play games or they sat and chatted or something but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Many people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 divide}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
 society into different social classes or groups - in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I suppose there was a good deal of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Could you tell me what the different ones were as far as you can remember?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, not really - it's only - well, I suppose it was the people who had a little bit more money than other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You would say this was the yard arm would you, money was the main thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I think so because it led to so much else, you see. It meant you could send your children to a better school and - I can't - rather difficult to explain -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Which class or group would you say you belonged to yourself at that time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I suppose we belonged to the working class - in a sense, all that - that's a very wide term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What sort of people belonged to the same working class gr
oup as yourself in those days. Can you think of some people and occupations you would have classed as being like yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 
That's difficult to answer too because - no, well what I was trying to think of was the girls I went to school with but then I 
don't really know what their parents were and they were - those that I did know were widely divergent so that - yes, you see my schoolfriend that I had latterly before I left school, her father was a ships captain, not a great big liner captain but - it w
as - it was a ship that used to sail into Belgium because I know he got some sort of a decoration at the beginning of the war and - who else - I can't think of who else - I don't - you see, I don't remem - I don't know what their parents did. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 See the - thin
gs weren't discussed then. Children didn't have so much to do with their parents and - you didn't ask those questions, you might be friendly with a girl all the years you were at school and you would never ask her what her father was, you'd get to know it
, perhaps she'd mention it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 But you wouldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 deliberately}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  go out of your way to find out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, you wouldn't - no. I mean, some of them - the - were schoolmasters. One girl in my form her - her father was the Headmaster of Banks Road school, I reme
mber that. While another girl had something to do with a - a firm that had a shop in Tar - a stationers shop in town but what she had - except the name was the same I don't know if they owned the shop or not. But I - I wouldn't have asked. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can yo
u remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What does that mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you remember your parents encouraging you to behave in a certain way towards certain class or type of person to another or were you encouraged to treat people all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, I think that's really how it is. You were always taught to be deferential to people older than yourself and - I suppose it was part of good manners to behave properly towards everybody. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not in that way because that was out of fashion long ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Were you ever taught to show respect - in the way you addressed people or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I can't remember particularly ex
cept, as I've said before, that you always were respectful to older people, especially anyone coming to the house. It was just sort of ordinary politeness I suppose. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember anyone you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. We never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these says?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, no, you see, by the time it came to my days people used that in the - sense of the way you do now, when you don't know anybody very well or - you know, the sort of thing, if the salesman comes to the door he calls you Madam, it doesn't mean a thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
In the district where you lived as a child who were considered the most important people at that time would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Who did the following people associate with do you think - shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about clergymen or teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And farmers and employers - any ideas on those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, the only thing I think is that they'd be friendly with the people in 
the same way of business probably. Or on the same - what they would think, social scale I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
But you've no thoughts about who they would think were on the same social scale as themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What sort of people would you say went to 
the church that you went to as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well certainly no I very rough people or poor people went because one of the first things I noticed when I changed my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 religion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  was that I went to a church where everybody went to whether they were poor or wheth
er they were rich, there was room for everybody. But from what I remember of my own childhood, I never remember seeing a poorly dressed person - or what I would call a rough person - especially in the old days when I can remember shawl people - but I can 
remember seeing shawl women in Esserex. This was a very big difference. I noticed it immediately. But no people of that type ever went to the churches that I went to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What sort of people would have gone to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Think they were pretty similar. As far as I remember, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was there any friction between Catholics and Protestants in that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, you see, I was brought up with all sorts of - wrong beliefs about Catholics. The things my parents said about them - you see, it wasn
't so much a difference of beliefs because they didn't know what Catholics believed - I don't know where they got their ideas from except I think it must have come from the Orangemen. Some of the things that my people said about Catholics were terrible an
d I don't know now how they could think it. Because I remember my father once saying, I never met a good Catholic in my life and if I did meet one he'd he better than his religion taught him to be. So what could you do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This is the sort of thing they said without even thinking you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, that - I think they just passed on what other people said. But the - and - I know they were up against some of the - what the things the Catholics believe in do but mostly it was a sort of prejudice,
 it was - not a - logical thing at all. Because I know when my father found out that I was going to be a Catholic he said he'd rather see me dead in my coffin. And what can you do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember ever seeing any friction between Protestants and Catholics?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I never saw any. The only thing I saw was the - the Orange bands come along because they used to come - one lot came from the north and one lot came from the south and they used to meet over opposite our house and they used to st
and there thumping their drums on the middle of a Sunday afternoon and then when they'd had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 enough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  they - turn round and went back home again. But - I never - never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 aw anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was it a particularly your father that felt like this about Catholics or
 was your mother the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, I can't really tell about that because - it was my mother who told me what my father had said, I never actually heard my father say it. And - he never said anything to me, one way or the other. But I only know that - 
they didn't speak to me or have anything to do with me for six months and when they met me in the street they ignored me. First of all they wee going to turn me out altogether and then they changed their minds. But from then on I was treated as a Pyriah.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This was when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
1920. I mean, after that - that's one reason why I don't know much of went on at home because they never consulted me, they never spoke toms and they never had anything to do with me and if we had visitors to the house they went in
to the sitting room and I was left down in the kitchen. Never had anything to do with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You don't think it was anything personal against the Catholic }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 faith}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 , it was just prejudice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well you see they didn't know anything much about it - I don't 
think they'd ever bothered to find out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Why do you think they felt so strongly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Don't know because there were a lot of people like that then. Well you see, I mean it's like the Orangemen are today. But I don't know how - how it came about but that's how it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What first attracted you to the Catholic faith - did you meet somebody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - yes, a girl that I was friendly with at school. When we got pretty well up in the school, there were - when we got into the sixth form there we
re only three of us and she and I were very friendly. This is the girl whose father was the ship's captain. And she told me that - at one time - must be something to do with where her father was sailing, she and her sister were sent a nursery and convent 
in Belgium for a certain time and that I think put it into their minds and when I was at school, her sister and brother were older than she was and they had both become Catholics and she was only waiting to be of age to please herself to do the same.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 She would be about what ago at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well she was - she was twelve months older than I was. But, you see, I left school and I lost touch with her. So when she was received I don't know but I know that she was. And I've only seen her on odd times 
since but that set me - got me interested and I - got some books and - and then when the people at home got the idea that I was tending that way they chased me off to see a Parson friend of theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This was when you were about sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh no, I 
was nineteen - eighteen or so. Anyway that didn't make any difference to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 They thought perhaps he might talk you out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, but he didn't. And - so I left it a bit and I was thinking about it for years I suppose. Anyway in the end was a 
mission at St Bernards, that was the parish church, so I went along - oh, I think I went to see the old Father Tyler, the old parish priest and he put me in touch with father Wright and I think Father Wright sent and said, she's been hanging around long e
n
ough, we'd better do something about it. So he - he made arrangements for me to meet him - if I was of interest - to meet him at Bishop Eaton on - Saturday afternoon, so I went up there. So then of course I just told the family that I'd done it and of cou
rse - the balloon went up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Where you lived as a child did all the people in the working class group have the same standard of living or were there different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I would say that some had more money than others. I would say that some of t
he children were better dressed than others because after all - different - occupations were better - some were better paid than others. I can't remember any particular ones but - naturally those that had a little bit more money - you could see the diff -
 they had new clothes more often or something like that but I don't think we bothered about it very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You talked about this girl she's father was a ships captain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What social class would you have put him in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And there was another girl who's father was a Headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh one of the girls in my form, he was the Headmaster of Banks Road school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What class would he be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well, I don't know how to name classes. Well, I suppose we would call them so
rt of professional classes Im - I - that's about the only way I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Within the working class group do you think there was one group which felt itself superior to the rest in any way? You said the working class group covers a tremendous section of the community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, it does. I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, definitely. That was really true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What would you say was the difference between those two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I sup
pose it was a matter of upbringing that - some parents were very particular how their children were brought up - I know my mother was and some were careless but not nearly like they are now. Because even people who were roughly brought up years ago knew h
o
w to behave themselves far better than a lot of the people who go about now think they're - well as we say, the whole cheese, of course then, in those days, I think divisions were more by way of the way you were brought up. Now it seems money. I feel that
.
 And you see, now it doesn't so much matter - if your father's a manual worker or a clerical worker or a professional man, if he's got - if your father has more money than the other well, you're the most important person. But in those days - if you belong
e
d to what we called the professional class the money part didn't seem to come into it. They didn't - there - no so much question. But you see now everybody'd after money and money seems to be the one thing that counts. So that you see in the old days wher
e
 you would not be accepted among people because your manners were bad and your upbringing was obviously bad, now you'll be accepted if you've got money which is quite different. Because you can't - now, in a way, you can't - keep - among sort of well brou
ght up people because where ever you go you find boors these days - I don't know whether you find that so - but I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It's not so cut and dried now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I think it mostly existed between the craftsman and the labourers in the course of their work. I don't know that it made - much difference otherwise but a craftsman definitely thought himself very superior to the unskilled man. Yes, ther
e was that difference - in their setting. But whether it - held so otherwise I don't - really know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well that's rather difficult to answer because - it does back t
o a sort of personal thing that my mother - always considered herself superior to my father. Yes, she always considered that she'd married beneath her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Why do you think she felt this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well I think she had a great idea of her own family. And thou
ght that they were good class people I suppose. And she didn't have that idea about my father's family. And she - that - that sort of ran through the whole upbringing part of it. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did she ever say this to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, quite a lot. Yes, more
 than she should have done I think. And - see, when I was very, very small, they may have gone out together, I can't remember, but as I got older I don't remember them going out much together at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 They }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  very close really in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 N
o. No, so that in that sense my family is not typical because - yes, my mother didn't go out a great deal but - I can't remember much of my father and mother going out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When I ask you did your mother think of herself as belonging to a particu
lar social class, what would you answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't know. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Whey did she feel this, was it because of her parents and her own background that she felt that she was superior to your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, I think so and I think she had a feeling
 that her family was better than his was because there were certain members of him family who were - well I didn't like them and I could understand that she didn't like them either and as I said to you before I thought my father was the best of the bunch.
 And she never cared much for his people and - and I certainly didn't care much - I hated his two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What was it about them that you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I didn't like them. Well I didn't like the youngest one because - she was the - she'd always p
romised - I'd lost my parents then - she had no family and when she died what she had was to be ours. Then she picked a quarrel with me when she died - she left all her money to her brother he died the next day. So, the money went to her brother's widow w
ho she loathed. Yes. And every penny of it has been spent. She - well she's dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and can you remember anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think it was easy. It - it would only have to be a 
case of - of a young person. Yes, it could be possible. If a young - person was clever and you see in those days you had to win scholarships or else have the money to provide your education you see, it all had to be paid for, well I can think - of someone
 who went to university, won his way through and became an eminent doctor and was eventually knighted. Don't remember whether he's dead now or not but he came out prominently during the war. And his father was just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 caretaker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  of a - a sort of - I don't k
now what you'd call it now 'cos they don't have those things - but a home where they took children and he would - the warden of this home until they were taken way to Doctor Barnardo's or somewhere. Well he was only a very ordinary everyday type of man bu
t his son definitely went to the head of his career so it was possible but I don't know that it happened very often. It had to be somebody exceptional. It didn't happen, not as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh yes. My mother would say that - somebody was a real lady. If someone that she knew - well, had an exceptionally attractive manner and - behaved }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 very}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  nicely. My mother always said she wanted us to be ladies, she always spoke like that becau
se - I often think now, when you hear children shouting and screaming and you get on the bus and they deafen you - my mother would say, but don't raise your voice. And if we ever said, as children do, that she shouted at us, she was most indignant. I do n
o
t shout, I may raise my voice, but I do not shout. And she was on those lines all the time. She particularly wanted us to grow up well behaved. And she was the - whether she had my father's people in mind about it I don't know but dad was very nice, I mea
n, he was a nice sort of a man and - in a lot of ways and I never - never remember my father raising his voice or - never remember him quarrelling or answering back or anything. Never. He was a - it's a pity about him really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember any parti
cular person being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, no, I can't - I can't - no - pin it down - I can't think of any particular instance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, always t
he policemen were on the beat. You could hear them, and in the night if you were awake you heard the Sergeant tapping his staff. You see, the Sergeant used to come round and meet the policeman on the beat at given places and if the - the policeman wasn't 
t
here when the Sergeant came you could here - there was something in that stick they carried and you could hear them tapping. And - must have - must have had something - yes. And then another thing that was very noticeable - the children playing in the str
e
et, of course the policeman was always after them you know, because of broken windows. And there'd always be one lad on the corner on watch. To see if the copper was coming along and then they'd be away up an entry or somewhere 'til he'd gone. And then wh
e
n he'd gone they'd all come out again. Oh yes, they were always round because - that's one reason why - burglaries - that's 'cos for other reasons burglaries were not so frequent but they didn't have the time to do them because the policeman was round. I 
c
onnected that a lot with the things that go on now. No, because they - these people have too long to do these things, they didn't before because the man was round. Even if they timed him and knew when he was due they wouldn't have time to do very much bef
ore he was due again. That's where I think the police are beaten now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
What did you think of the police generally - were you ever threatened with the police when you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did you think about policemen as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I don't know, I - I always thought of them as protective and - I suppose that safety depended on them. I never remember speaking to one but - I mean, it - they were much a familiar figure walking along the road - because they came along all the streets 
and - and that. Well I don't think I've seen only one policeman walking up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Grant Avenue{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in the twelve years we've lived here. But we all - we had a great respect for the police. And even the children had because in those days the policeman would give a child what they call a lift under the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 listener}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  and - they'd go along - lift under the listener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Is that what they called it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh, they called - all sorts of names for things. But they just boxed their ears and send them off and there was none of this - juvenile court business, that I remember like it is now. You see, the policeman had more freedom to - to box the kids ears.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 He did it on the spot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. Yes. And the kids had a wholesome fear of them although they - they tried to take the rise out of them. They were scared of them. Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How do you think he treated people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I never heard any criticism of them like you hear now. I don't ever remember hearing any criticism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was your home rented when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I didn't. Well as a matter of fact I think the houses were in the hands of an agent. And the rent was paid to the agent and if you wanted anything you just went down to the agent's office and made a complaint. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Do you ever remember hearing your parents speaking of the landlord and what kind of a person he was and what they felt about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well you - the landlord that I remember of that house we were in so long was
 a Mersey pilot - and he was drowned in a - a very bad pilot boat, I don't remember if it was an accident but it was at the beginning of the first world war. I - I don't know what happened to the pilot boat but there were a lot of pilots drowned and he wa
s
 one of them. Yes. And I remember - just vaguely remember him. He lived in the next block. We lived at 54 and he lived at 44. And he owned the property and then his wife after that and then she handed it over eventually to agents and we lost touch with th
em after that. But my mother thought quite a lot of Mr Bonnard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well yes, money was always scarce, you know we never had - never - things were never very easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did you feel about it was a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well we just had to be very careful with everything and - and then of course in those days there wasn't the same amount of dissatisfaction - if you couldn't have a thing well you didn't have it. And - I had to go 
without a lot of things, I mean, my parents struggled to put me to a good school, I couldn't have all the things the other children had. But then again, in those days, when education had to be paid for, they didn't bring out so many frills like they do no
w. Although I went to a good school we didn't have all these frills of uniforms and things like that. We had to have a certain kind of - gym dress and a blouse and we were supposed to wear a dark coat and of course we wore the school hat and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 colours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  and things but beyond that, you were quite free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 They didn't demand so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, they didn't. And they didn't seem to go in for expensive activities or anything, although we had all sorts of interesting things on. But - so much money wasn't expected of
 people in that way and I think its so strange that they should have - stopped asking people to pay for the education and now mother's are complaining of the money they've got to spend on - things that are not really necessary. It costs them far more now 
to buy all these frills than it cost my people to pay for me to go to school. It's strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Doesn't make sense does it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill or out of work? Can you remember any instances when either - of these things happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, I don't remember dad being ill. But - and of course latterly until the whole thing folded up - after the first world war I don't think he was home until about - oh, of course things were bad during the slump in the '20's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Up to 1918 can you remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well when I was very young I do remember it but not - not after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Can you remember what difference it made to the family when he was out of work when you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well my mother did things to help out. She either did sewing for people or - and then - as I said before, she had these - Cunard Officers used to come and stay and I remember that was - these brass things were brought from India by a Cunard Captain. Y
es. He's dead now - Captain Finlay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So this helped things out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. Yes. And she did that because we had room in the house you see, it was a bigger house than we really needed and she had people like that and - that came odd times. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can
 you remember your parents ever getting help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. Well there wasn't so much of that, there was no what they call now Social Security or anything. 'Cos in the bad days when I was very young and my
 father was out of work there was no unemployment of any kind - there was nothing. Only they had good friends and I do know that friends helped them 'cos I can remember once when I was very small and I had the measles, I remember that. And I remember frie
nds being very good to my mother, helping her out, then. Because there was nothing you see, if he wasn't working there was nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
How would these friends have helped would they have given money or brought things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Brought things I think, as far 
as I remember. I don't think there was - as far as I remember there was no money in it, I mean, as far as I knew, but there again you see, I didn't know everything. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
When there was someone in the district the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it - do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music as it was called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh no, because you didn't have that - not as far as I can remember. You don't - you never heard your neighbours or - I mean,
 we were - lived in this big - sort of main street and then there were the small streets opposite and we used to have to go up them to go to the tram and that but - I never remember hearing any noise or - people didn't, you know, even - even what we calle
d
 then very rough people didn't behave like the people do now. It's very difficult to explain if you haven't lived through it. And - and then you see again - to a great extent the people that we looked upon as really rough people seemed to be more in parts
 
of the town. For instance, we used to say the Princes Road was like a barrier. He didn't care so very much for the people who lived on the far side towards the docks. Well you see, when the war began and the damage - the second war - and the damage was do
n
e down that part all the people came up and that's what spoilt Liverpool. That part - that was the beginning - that was the beginning of it because we noticed then immediately because even the people who lived in these small houses like this in the side s
t
reets were all very respectable people and lived more or less in a similar kind of way but when these - what we call the rougher people - cane over, it spoilt it all. And then of course after that the - the - the people who had the money got out of the di
s
trict altogether and we found ourselves left in it. We didn't know what to do. Because was only my sister and I then. And she had these students. She was getting fed up with them and she said I don't know we'll have to do. We'll have to get out of here. A
n
d then of course you couldn't rent a house so the upshot of it was that she spent part of the money my father left her and I spent part of my savings and we bought this house between us just to get out of the place. And we've never gone back. Only when th
e bus takes us along Princes Road. But when I think of the way that was when we were children it breaks my heart to go there now. Yes, because it really was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Were you given lessons by one of yours parents, a tutor or a governess or did you go straight to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well at five I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
And when you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well nine o'clock it al
ways was - school. And then there was the dinner hour. Twelve to half past one I think. And then half past one to four o'clock I think - at the first school I went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You went for the whole day when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You didn't go for half a day at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What kind of school was the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh it was an ordinary council school, the nearest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was it mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes. Well when I say mixed, it was - mixed only so far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Up to a certain age group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, the very little chil}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 dren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  - little ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Up to seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
How let me think - it would be about that because - we were in the infants for about three years I should think and then we went to another part of the school that was called the juniors and I
 was there for a year. Yes, and there were boys there because the boys sat on one side and the girls on the other side. And then when we went up into the seniors the boys had a school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So it would be slightly older than seven then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, it would be probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh it was only few minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Who would have taken you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - my mother took me when I first went and - we always laughed about this afterwards - she asked a ch
ild in the street who was already going to school if she would bring me home. I didn't know about this. I arrived home and presently the child arrived in great terror because she couldn't find me anywhere and I'd got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I can imagine her fears can't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes, especially when my mother was - yes, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
After a little while did you go by yourself or did your mother continue to take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh no, she only took me the first day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You had your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I must have liked it - I had two - I have no remembrance of disliking it at all so I suppose I just accepted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No strong feelings either way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about the teachers at this first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I just vaguely remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What was your general feeling about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - I liked them and - yes, I liked them very much indeed. And I can remember them when I first went to school when
 there were long flowing dresses with trains at the back and they had a metal thing that hung down from their waist and clipped the - the back of the dress up and kept it from sweeping the floor and I can remember that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did the teachers emphasise 
certain things as Important in life - such as manners and tidiness - punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I can't remember that the teachers did that. I think in those days it was more done at home - I think your parents did it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about punctuality and tidiness at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - everybody was so I don't remember - if there was anything about it in school it was sort of accepted thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can't remember - they 
had their ways of punishing you but I can't remember - oh you - they kept you in. But I don't remember that I was ever kept in. But I think they used to keep them in for about half an hour or something at night time but - I had a experience of it so I don
't really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You can't remember what sort of thing they'd be kept in for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Were the girls treated the same way as the boys as regards being punished or was there a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 In the first school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, always. Because, as I told you before about - my father was a great reader and - in a way, what I suppose you would call now to a grea
t extent, a self educated man because he was really interested in literary things and - and probably just the same way because - we were - as soon as we were ever able or - old enough, I don't know what the age was, we had to join the library and bring bo
o
ks home and we had to read Scott and Dickens and Thackeray and all these people from quite an early age and I can remember when I was expected to do things in the house which I always was expected to and my mother used to call me and I'd be buried in a bo
ok as she used to say and she'd say - I'll take that book from you if you don't go and do - whatever it was, and I can remember her snatching the book off me. I was so buried in the book you know. And - she of course had to be practical. It was funny.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did they ever visit this first school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, they'd - no, there was nothing of that then - no. Your mother took you at the beginning but - the only other time they ever went is if - I seem to remember them putting on some little sh
ows or other but I've a very vague recollection of it but I think the parents must have come because I don't what otherwise we'd have done it for. Yet I can't just remember. But the mothers never had anything to do with the teachers. They only knew what y
ou brought home and - I suppose they only knew their names by hearing you say - they didn't bother at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did the other children in this first school come from similar types of home to your own or no.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I suppose they did, I don't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did 
the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I don't think so, I think they were scrupulously fair as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, they weren't heard of in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No I don't think so..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You did go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You went to Aigburth. Aigburth Vale. What kind of school was this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well it was called the secondary school - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Aigburth{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Vale{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}High school{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. A.V.H.S. of course. 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Aigburth{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Vale{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}High School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 because A.V.H.S. was on all your things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It wasn't mixed was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 About two miles wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. Well - at first - I - had to walk. I walked there in the morning and stayed for my midday meal there and then walked home at night. But I didn't like staying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What was the food like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh it was very good. Of cour
se it was not a big school. I forget now how many - girls there were there when I went - it had only been open two years and - I - I think there were about two hundred and sixty or something when I left but the food was very good and the cooking was very 
good and it was very - it was really done very nicely - the food wasn't just put all on a plate and given to you - the dishes were put on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 able and you served yourself with it. Yes, it was really very nicely done because there - there was a cook there -
 of course the - the dining room and the kitchen were all built in in the school - they had their own cook and their own maids there. And - but I wanted to come home. So we found out then that I could get a tram from Aigburth Vale to Park Place and then I
 walked home up Upper Hill Street and had my dinner and then I walked all the way back. Used to take me all my time - I was only home a few minutes. And then eventually I got a bicycle. And then I came home all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So then you came home for lunches for most of your school life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did you think of this school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, I liked it very much. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh I liked them. You see, in that school it w
as different from the other. You have a different mistress for different subjects, you had your form mistress and then all the other subjects were taken by different mistresses so you had a little bit of all them really. And then you had your own special 
form mistress and - I liked - one specially I liked very much, I had her - twice if not three times as a form mistress. And she was very nice, I liked her very much. She died soon after I left the school. She died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was she an older woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, she
 was only quite young, she wasn't - hadn't long qualified from the university. She was in mathematics and I don't know what happened to her but she went into bad health and she was only about forty when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did the teachers at this school emphasise certain things as important in life?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, they looked at things differently in a way. They looked at the social side and the way you behaved out of school and all that far more than they did in the elementary school that I first went to. They we
re very strict about you wearing your gym dress on gym days but not on any other day. And - similarly your gym shoes. You couldn't wear those, you had to have ordinary slippers. And you didn't go on the polished floor in anything but your slippers. They w
ere very particular about that because it was beautiful inlaid - lay - you know, what you may call it - floors. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh you were pulled up life you said anything the least bit - out of place or bad grammar or - or a
nything at all. Oh yes. They were very particular - the Headmistress was very particular. And very particular about the way you came out. The mistress stood at the dressing room door and you had your hat on and your gloves on and your coat buttoned and ev
e
rything before you got out and - they were very particular because some of the mistresses used to go across the park and if they saw anybody doing anything they shouldn't do or dressed the way they shouldn't be they were in trouble when they got into scho
ol. Yes, they were very particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
If you did something the teachers disapproved of at this school what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well, if it was something where it was just a matter of being told off you got that but if you broke one of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 rules}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  that was 
- was punishable by what they called a detention then you had detention on Friday night for an hour and one of the mistresses took it and you had to go - they all went into one form room and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What would you have had to have done for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well 
I don't know - I can't remember now but there were different things that you knew - and of course if you - rude or - made a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 nuisance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  of yourself in any way - but you had to be pretty bad - a mistress would give you detention on the spot and you'd have to s
tay in and - if your work was very bad you might have got one and you might have had to stay in and do it again or something like that. I think that was about the only punishment had - only lines - of course you got lines to write. Sometimes of course you
r detention was taken up writing your lines out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents show interest in your work at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes. Yes, very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Would they ask you what you did at school and visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well the Head
mistress - was sort of at home, as far as I remember, every Tuesday afternoon and if any mother, or father if it came to that, wanted to know anything or any questions they could always come and see the Headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 On that particular afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
On that afternoon, yes. But I don't remember - connection between any of the other mistresses except that we had rather interesting things at that school and then the parent did meet teachers. They had what they called little garden parties and things be
cause the school had its own grounds, we didn't have to go anywhere else. Its - well of course it's altered all now but it still is on its own grounds but a lot more buildings have been put and taken the ground up. When I was there there was a lot of grou
n
d. And we - almost every summer in summer term we had something - we had a flower garden party one time and we all had to wear different kind of flowers and - we had - in 1912 - the centenary of Dickens birth we had a Dickens entertainment and then - then
 they had a Shakespeare one and then we had - we had different things at - yes, and all the parents came. I know we had on thing once - I can't remember exactly what it was but know our form had to do a caf\'e9
 part of it and we had to see to all the refreshments and - different forms did different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 So there were lots of activities connected with the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. There were quite a lot. Yes. And then the Headmistress always used to give a sort of at home at - at Christmas time. The end of the Christmas term and we all went in the evening all dressed up and danced and things but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would the parents come to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. They didn't go to that. And then - we used to have a - a speech day too about Christmas time and we all had to go in whi
te - no colours had to be worn - we all had white dresses, all the mistresses were in evening dress and a lot of the education committee people came onto the platform and some very important person gave the prizes. And they were prizes worth having. For -
 senior {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 because I got honours. And then the next year I was due for one when I got my matric but then the war was on and they gave you a - a sort of scroll. I don't know where it is now. Here it is - I have got it - I've got me matric certificate and
 my - senior Oxford certificate - I've got them still, yes. And I would have had another one the following year only we had to give them up as a war effort. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 They were probably all better off than we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You felt this did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well yes, because - they - they had more money to spend than I ever had and - but it wasn't a difficulty, I - it didn't worry me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It didn't have any effect on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. And then you see, they - they weren't snobbish or anything. You weren't - sort of isolated because you couldn't do things. You were never made to feel small or anything. But I do remember that in one form there was some trouble about some new girls w
ho came and they - suppose they didn't think they was nice as they were and there was a bit of spitefulness when on. I heard about it. And the Headmistress had them all - I suppose into her office and laid the law down about it and said that sort of thing
 shouldn't be. But I remember hearing about it but it didn't happen in my form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
But this was because the girls felt they weren't as nice as they should have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 The new girls weren't as nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did the tea
chers single out some children for different treatment from the others in this school - can you remember any instance of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 In any way at all - was anyone treated differently from anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not in the ordinary way. Ther
e were different divisions in forms for different things but that was a - a scholastic different more than anything else. That's the only thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there any gangs or groups in this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think so - not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Nearly eighteen. I was eighteen a few months later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have stayed longer if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  had the opportunity - there wouldn't have been any necessity would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, well, you see, what actually happened was - my parents wanted me to go on to university and there was a means then, my father pulled some strings, by which I could have got a grant which - of course they didn't do it like they do it n
ow. And they were hoping for me to go on to university and I got my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 matriculation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  which then was the entrance exam you see. And - then - of course the war had been on a little while and there was my brother younger and my mother had great ideas about him a
nd what he was to be and I said to myself - it's more important for a man to have a career than it is for me. So I packed up the whole thing and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Was this the main reason you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. I didn't - even finish the year out. I finished at the Eas
ter of 1916 and said I'd look for a job of some sort. And of course it wasn't so easy then but the Headmistress helped me. She told me of a firm where a cousin of hers - young cousin of hers had gone and - she made arrangements for me and got me in. And t
h
ey'd only just begun taking girls in. It was a man's place really and they sort of hardly knew how to treat the girls and - well some of them were older in the office 'cos they'd always had men and they only took - they were only taking girls because they
'd lost their men being called up, you see, so I - I decided that was the best way to do because it would have meant three or four more years even if I'd have got a grant I'd have had to be kept so I thought the best thing to do was to pack it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did your parents think about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well they must have agreed as far as I knew. I don't remember about - it - I don't remember. So that was the end of my scholastic career.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you attend any part time education afterwards - any evening classes
 or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. The only think I did do for a short time was - from the office they paid for me to go to - now what was it called then, it was somewhere in the old Exchange Buildings - to learn Spanish because they had a lot of dealings with Spanis
h firms and they had Spanish correspondence and I went for a while and that's how I met - Winifreds grandfather. He taught me Spanish. Yes. Doctor Azurdi, that's how - and you see, after a while I decided to ask him if he would take me privately you see, 
and he said yes. But when I got to the house he passed it on to Leonores sister - the older one, Marie Teresa and I became friendly with her. And I've known them since then. That was 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well I have
 a regret that I wasn't able to go any further with it but I'm very grateful that - I had the education I did have because although I've never been able to use it from a material point of view, if you like to put it that way, its been a great help to me b
e
cause - well the Latin helped me. I mean, I've always loved Latin and that helped me, especially in church and all that sort of thing, 'course that's what I'm feeling now. And the French helped me because when I went to France I could manage to find my wa
y
 round and do - dictation sor of Eng - sort of French and have - have some funny experiences to like when I went up - up the end of the Elysee in France the first time I went, I was walking down there and I didn't know where I was going to get the bus bac
k. So I say a gendarme man at the end there and I walked all round making this sentence up, because you see, I hadn't actually used French since the time I left school. And I didn't arrive in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France
{\*\xmlclose} until '49 because although I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Switzerland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in - so I
 was glad about my education from that point of view. Yes, and I loved knowing from - from Latin and things like that I loved knowing that much. Oh and I learnt a little bit of Greek as well. I can tell the meaning of works without always having to used a
 dictionary and know their origins and things like that and I find it very interesting. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You would agree that you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It's helped you appreciate other things in life since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. And it's helped me - when I've mixed with people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 who\rquote ve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  had a similar education I felt -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You'd got something in common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Exactly. You see, because I miss it when I've got to speak to somebody who perhaps doesn't know as much - I've got to be careful. I suppose most people would find that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You find you have so much in common to talk about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And you don't have to watch yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. But of course now with the younger people they all have more - opportunities though I don't say they're as well educated but they certainly have more opportunities than people had years ago. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Then it was the exception to push on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. Yes. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Whilst you were at school did you have any part time job or anything that you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No, I don't think that sort of thing was thought of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
This first job that your Headmistress got for you - what exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
It was clerical work. It was - oh, it was book keeping. Yes, I was in the books department. For two - two years was it - '16 - '18 - yes for two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What hours did you work at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Half past nine 'til - I think it would be half past five but I know it was half past nine in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about Saturday and Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well you had to go in Saturday morning then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Just Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Never Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you have a half day in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Just the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, I must have had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What year would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 1916. I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You think you had holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, I must have had holidays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember what you were paid in this first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh I got the magnificent sum of twelve shillings a week when
 I went there first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 At the time did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I suppose I thought so because I'd had nothing to do with that kind of life. I suppose I didn't really know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Nothing to compare it with you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, what wage
s would be. I only know that I didn't - I wasn't old enough to remember people being - well, myself being paid in gold. And I remember a woman in the office, her mother died and she had a little hoard of gold and she let me have a half sovereign. So I had
 the half sovereign for years, my sister has it now. She had the half sovereign and eventually later in another way I got a sovereign so I got a sovereign, she's got a half sovereign.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you give any of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 twelve\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  shillings to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh 
she must have had all of it and she'd just give me back - I don't remember how much, I can't remember now at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What would you have spent it on - the amount you had back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Don't know. I probably didn't get enough back to make it worthwhile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh very well. Yes, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - you didn't see very much of - you see, the firm was run by about three men who were Directors and had their o
wn private office. Well, you only saw them if they sent for you and it was a very, very rare thing for them to do so I saw very little of them. They'd walk through perhaps and just say good morning to you. You mostly worked for the man who was the head of
 your department.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How would be treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Oh, very well, he was a queer sort of a man but I got on very well - so long as you did your work well, that was what mattered, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about him and the Directors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well that - th
e people who were at the head of the place I never bothered about at all because as I say I never saw them but - the man I immediately worked for was very nice and then there was a man in another department, he was in the correspondence - did a lot of the
 Spanish things and he used to talk to me and - when I - he knew I was learning a bit of Spanish he used to practice a little bit with me and that and I just remember him but - otherwise we got on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about the work - did you like it or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I didn't like it - because when I was at school the one subject I couldn't do was maths and science and things like that. I was always the bottom because I can remember the look of pity the science mistress used to have on her face 
when the exam results came out and she used to look at the results on the notice board in the form room and she'd see me top for history, top for French, top for Latin, pretty well up for geography and right at the bottom for maths and science and she use
d to be very sorry for me. So - I go into an office and I'm doing figures all the time, figures and it was the one thing that I couldn't do and hated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did the job alter your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5842211\charrsid793154 attitude}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think so. No I never thought of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You were with this firm for two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What made you leave them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I - I joined the - with he Women's Army. But what made me do it I honestly cannot tell you. I've no recollection where I got the information from or anything. The first of it that I can remember was going to some place in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for a medical - the first I'd ever had in my life. And being passed and going to a - a depot near {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Oldham{\*\xmlclose}
. And the thing about it is I never moved out of the depot because they want
ed a clerk as soon as I got there and they put me in the company office - figures again, I was doing money and pays and - going to the Bank once a week and bringing the pay out, sitting next to the pay officer and doing all the money and all the balances 
and all that sort of thing. And they kept me there you see, I never went on draft to a - a unit of any kind. 1918, you see, well it was pretty late -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Were you a W.R.A.C.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well - W.A.A.C. W.A.A.C. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How long would you have been in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I was there from the - the May of 1918 and I was out in the December of 1919 - because the war was over, you see, and I didn't when I went up it would be over so soon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Can you remember what you were paid in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I can't remember w
hat it started with - but then again - when they put me permanently in this pay office - they gave me - whatever did they call it - oh, they, it - people who were - well I seem to think - I think I got about eighteen shillings a week or something like tha
t
. I know it was a good deal more - because I had my keep as well. And then I think I had some rises because I did - I considered I was quite well paid because I had my uniform as well, 'cos we didn't have - they didn't have suits like they had in this war
,
 we had a dress and a - a big coat and they were rather nice dresses. And - a little bit - was fastened up to here and had a little collar and the - the ordinary people had a brown collar and khaki dress and the - the corporal like we were or sergeants or
 anything they had them - a white collar or tussel collar and we had a little badge on our arm and we - we had a new dress every so often, I forget now when it was. But they were quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you send any money home to your mother whilst you were in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't think so, I don't remember that I did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You said you had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 good fun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  there with the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes, we had good fun, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How did you feel about the work - it was figures again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Figures again, but I didn
't - but I didn't mind it by that time - I'd got sort of used to it and - I didn't mind it because I had records to keep and - all payments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It was more varied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes it was, there was quite a lot of things to do and - I found it interesting. And then we worked with the officers you see, the orderly room and - and that and it was quite nice - quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did having this job in the army alter your attitude to school in any way?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think I ever altered my ideas. Not until I saw the way
 they changed it and then messed it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What did you do after you came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you see, there were no jobs then. You see, all the men who'd been in the Army had no jobs. After the first world war it was pretty awful because men were walking th
e streets and - coming round selling things. I think half the Army came round selling writing pads and note paper and - and you didn't want it and - you wanted to help them and you couldn't help everybody and - and you know it was - it was pretty awful af
ter the first world war and - there wasn't very much done as far as I remember. And - I suppose the men must have gone on the dol}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  'cos they had it by that time I think - for men but not for women. But I don't know, 'course not being a man and - I know that
 it was very, very difficult to get a job. And I came home in the December and I didn't get a job 'til the following September. And then I got it through a woman that I though perhaps if I learnt typing it might be a - addition to typing and shorthand so 
I
 answered an advertisement in the paper and took some lessons from a women. I wasn't very good at it and I didn't like it and then one day she said to me, a friend of mine took a job and now she's decided against it. Would you like to go and see if you ca
n get it? Because I'd tried all over the place but I couldn't get anything to do. So I went and I got the job. And when I got in it I said to myself, five minutes in this place will be the limit. I was there forty years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What kind of firm was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
It was a - a wholesale clothing manufacturers firm and it was jut on the point of expansion. There were only about sixty people there when I went into this office and there was only the one girl and she left after a week - she only had a week to show me 
all the things then I was there on my own. And then they opened up, they bought a - a building next door and put more machines in and then eventually there were two more girls came in the office and - they - the first manager was - only a rough sort of a 
man but he was very clever as a cutter and - that sort of thing. And he was a good manager and - I got on very well with him. And when he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 ground}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  out I knew what I was talking about he left a lot of things to me and - he was very good because if I made a sli
p he always covered me. He was very, very good and I'd been there twelve years when he died. And after that me troubles began. Whether they wore jealous because he'd treated me so well I don't know, but everybody seemed to be against me after that. And ye
t
 they relied on me for everything. And - things weren't so good after that. The two men who followed were my enemies the whole time they were there. And yet they depended on me. But every blasted thing, because I ran the whole office and did all the facto
r
y returns, all the wages and all the trade board requirements and doctors examinations and factory inspectors and returns of work and all the insurances and then later on when taxes came out for ordinary people I had all that to do and - all connections w
i
th - Labour Exchanges when they were short - time or - take an - taking people on and stopping and - oh, everything - everything to do with a small factory. And I liked it because it was a responsibility and - it was a job that I really could take an inte
rest in. And right up to the end, even though I felt as if I was fighting the people all the time, I still liked it. And when the second - war began and I used to have to give orders to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 travellers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  - and they came and they - the cotton - the man who came fro
m the cotton firm said, well look, you're going to be short, you'd better get this, that and the other thing and I got this that, and the other thing you can have. Of course they got very friendly with me. He got me all this stuff and one of the Dirextors
 
came down - he carried on about it. But I saw afterwards what his point was. He was sorry that he hadn't done it and he was mad mad because I'd had the chance to do it and the same thing happened over machine parts for the single - sewing machines. They s
a
id to me when they knew what was coming, send us an order for three months for all that you'll need. And I did. And I kept plentiful supply and we were never short of a part all the while the war was on and then they criticized that afterwards. Most disap
pointing because I flet as though I was running the firm for them and fighting them all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No. I think I really - settled myself down to that and didn't bother so much about the figures 
really. As the other side of it and then the only - it was worrying because I had a lot of money and I had to balance it up every time and then they'd send somebody down every now and again to check up so I daren't be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 caught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  on the hop and I felt they were
 watching me all the time and yet they trusted me that's what I couldn't make out. And - I - I really was interested in it and - I - I sort of gave myself up to it and I never bothered about anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training p
eriod for any of your jobs? In the first job you would just sort have gone in and learnt as you went along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And this would have applied to this job as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well I was just one week with the girl who - who - who was there who was
 leaving and then she - handed over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Interests in what way? I suppos
e we wouldn't - no. Well, the reason why I didn't know very much about the Directors who ran my firm was the headquarters were not in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}
. So that I only saw a Director who used to come over once a week for an afternoon just to sort of have a pow-wow
 with the manager and see how things were going ; I got very friendly with him - he was very nice with me. He was about the nicest of all until he died. He was always good to me. Because if he wanted me to do anything he was always asking me to do somethi
ng extra and he was always telling me all the stones in my crown I was going to get. But I didn't have anything much to do with then and for years I'd never even been to the head office. We didn't have much connection with them at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you feel that there was a division of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I don't know because I didn't really have very much to do with the girls in the machine rooms except - if there - I had to see them for certain things and - help them out sometimes with things.
 It gave me a good opportunity to help people. Well, for instance, if anybody was ill and went to hospital I used to go and see there and make sure they got their wages and - if anybody was in any trouble and wanted some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 letters writing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154  because some of the
m were very illiterate, they could always bring them to me. They were always coming to me with - little things like that and I found I was able to do a lot of that sort of thing over the years and I liked that as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Some people say that in those da
ys there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - there - that didn't arise because you see both the girls and the boys were taken as apprentices and they had to have a certificate because I 
had to fill in the certificate and send it to some place in London, some trade boards or something and it was sort of registered and - they had to serve four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 To get this certificate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well, they got the certificate and then - you see, then
 it was sent of - up after the four years and at the fourth year, you see, they had a rise every year in wages and when they became eighteen - starting at fourteen - when they were eighteen they were counted as grown up and they were on what they called t
he minimum rates. You see and the same - same applied to men although we didn't have so many men. Well, you see, the men just cut the garments out and the girls made them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, I - I don't think so. Sort of - you took those things for granted and didn't think about them. No. I suppose I wasn't interested. I was just interested in me work and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you continue to live at home when you first started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes. Well there was a time when I thought I wasn't going to have to after 1920? You see, they said that they - couldn't stay at home any more but then - they must have had a pow-wow between each other and decided I could stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about with your brother and sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well you see - my brother went away to serve his apprenticeship and - I don't - 1902 - 19 - 19 - oh, he went away I thin
k while I was still in the forces - 1918. Or something like that. And then he came home. Well, he was out of a job and then of course he got this complaint that nobody seemed to know anything at all about and he never worked again. And you see, he was jus
t
 a drag on everything and - that made things difficult. He was a very difficult character. I never got on with him and this sickness made it worse and things were - very difficult, very difficult indeed. And - of course my mother expected me to pay up and
 
you see she was so taken with him that she couldn't - see - what I would call sensible things. She used to speak to me as though he was the one that was bringing the money in and not me. Because part of that time in the slump after the war when my father 
w
as only working ever now and again and my brother never worked at all I was the only one that was bringing any money in. And yet she spoke as though he was the one that was bringing the money in. So it was - things were not easy. And then you see, with th
e other upset between them I was always out on a limb, I was never in a way - in - it never - in one sense I can say that I've never been sort of settled at home although I've lived at home. There's always been that difference. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you spend your 
Sunday any differently when you first started work - did you stop going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Yes, but I don't know when I stopped going to Sunday school. Oh, that must have been when I - when I joined the Army that must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You were still going to Sunday school when you first started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I - the reason why I think I must have been is because I remember the girl I was friendly with. And she had three brothers in the Army. Four brothers altogether. And every time they name home on leave
 there was a little party and it - I was thinking of it after you wee here the other day, and you said what sort of things did we do and I remember her parties and the games we used to play. And - I - I can't think how we did some of them but I can rememb
e
r the names of them. Her father was a very good organizer and he had us all organized and we used to play games and have huge fun. Well that was while the war was on because she lost one brother - in the war. But I don't remember being friendly with her a
f
ter I came home. So that - makes me think - and then you see, I got interested in - in Catholic things as I left school because of this girl I'd got friendly with at school and she went on to the university you see but I didn't. And then with me going awa
y in the Army I lost touch with her and I've only seen her an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid359101\charrsid793154 odd time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
 ever since. And - that made a difference because I didn't want to go - anymore to church or anything. I used to sneak out and go to some Catholic church if I could. But I had to be very careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
In 1916 when you were eighteen ad just started work - did you go to church at all? To the church of England - did you go in the morning or evening at all On - Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I would - would be an evening I think if the family went and if my mo
ther insisted on us going I suppose I'd go but I don't remember going very regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I never have done. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No interest at all in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You would have been too young to vote before 1919 wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes. Oh, when did women get votes? Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 1918 at the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Was it as long ago as that we had votes? I don't remember. That show how interested I am in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 If you had voted what party do you think you would have voted for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well I don't know - if it had been someone we knew about or someone we knew good things about, might have voted for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 This would have been a personal thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It might have been but if - if 
it was a case of having to vote and not knowing anything about anything of them I suppose I'd have voted Conservative for safety. But certainly not Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I know you didn't have a great deal of spare time while you were at school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things now you were working - how would you spend your spare time when you first started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Well, no - well - when I was at - after the war when I went to t
his firm I used to bring a lot of work home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 What about before the war - up 'til 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I think things were pretty much the same, I don't remember - any - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Would you have gone out anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh, I joined a tennis club. Oh, and I play
ed in a hockey club too after I left school. It was the mistress that I told you I liked so much played in a hockey club I knew that because when she played hockey with us she had - red stripe on her skirt and a red and blue tie and she - used to ask a gi
r
l in one of the forms above me sometimes to complete a side for the team she played for. That's how I got to know. So when I left I wrote to her and she got me to join her club and I played with them until I left - Liverpool to go into the Army and of cou
rse after that I didn't go to it again. But I joined the tennis club that the Azurdias got up and I played with them. Oh that was until I went into the Army, well I played a little while. Yes, after I came out. I played until they went back to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Guatemala{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And then other people began to join the club that I didn't care for so I dropped out. So I didn't play again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Did you go out in the evening at all apart from playing tennis and hockey? Didn't go out very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you make new friends at this time when you first started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
Well - yes, I was friendly with the girls I worked with in that office in town because in the summer we used to go out to Guineagat baths, I remember that. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And in the first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 I don't remember anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Very rarely. Very rarely. We were never encouraged. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Where would you go with this friend you had made - was there anywhere you w
ould have gone together or done together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 It's all sort of vague to me, I can't remember. Very much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Did your parents ever meet your friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
I can't remember whether I knew people from the office ever came home - I don't remembe
r that. But I know that sometimes I used to bring girls home with me when I was in the forces, for a weekend sometimes. I - they seemed to like me to bring someone home with me then, I did that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 When you were out did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh yes. Definitely. And I had to be back - well I suppose 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}}ten o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 or that you weren't allowed out later. Not unless it was - a special occasion or anything. Well, when I used to go to the parties at - during the war time with this gi
rl I was friendly with and stayed there fairly late then, somebody always brought me home - somebody living near. To me, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 May I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
But then they shouldn't my name because if it's not supposed to be personal. I hope not because I
 don't want it to be personal. Because you see it seems like - asking questions that you wouldn't normally be asked, you know, sort of private questions. You feel as though you're sort of being quizzed and it doesn't matter if your name doesn't go down to
 it because you've all those particulars go down. It seems different somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Could I have your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Single.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh that was - Buckley - Finchill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 Oh - I can't remember. I was born at my grandmother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7618658 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 You weren't there - long were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6430172 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5839449\charrsid793154 
No, my mother was only staying there for while I was born. And then she - we came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}. And seeme
